Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 450 degrees. Dice the @sweet potatoes{12%ounce} into 1/2-inch cubes. Toss the cubes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place the baking sheet in the oven to roast for ~{20-25%minutes}, tossing halfway through cooking, until soft and slightly caramelized.

Prep the veggies: Meanwhile, halve, peel, and dice the @yellow onion{1}. Pick the @cilantro{¼%ounce}(leaves picked of the stems). Cut the kernels off the @corn on the cob{1}. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Zest, then halve the @lime{1}. Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%box}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a large #pan{} over medium heat. Add the onion and cook, tossing for ~{5-6%minutes}, until softened and slightly caramelized. Season with salt and pepper. Add the garlic, corn, and half the black beans to the pan and cook, tossing for another ~{3-4%minutes}. Wrap the @flour tortillas{6} in #tin foil{} and place in the oven to warm for ~{5%minutes}.

> HINT: Save the remaining black beans for another recipe!

Add the roasted sweet potatoes, @honey{1%jar}, @cumin{1%teaspoon}, and the juice of half a lime to the pan and cook, tossing for ~{2-3%minutes} to combine. Season with salt and pepper.

Halve and pit the @avocado{1}. Thinly slice one half and set aside; scoop the other half into a #small bowl{}. With a fork, mash the avocado with @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, the remaining lime juice, and the lime zest. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Assemble the tacos: Fill the tortillas with the sweet potato filling, avocado slices, avocado-lime crema, and cilantro leaves.